A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Georgia Speech-Language-Hearing Association; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia Speech-Language-Hearing Association is a professional
4 organization that supports speech-language pathologists (SLPs), audiologists, and speech,
5 language, and hearing scientists in the State of Georgia and works to advance the interests
6 of those professions and the public through education, mentoring, advocacy, resources, and
7 service to ensure communication for all; and
8 WHEREAS, many Georgians have communication disorders, language impairment or
9 hearing disorders, or swallowing and feeding disorders; and
10 WHEREAS, many of these disorders are caused by various things such as genetics, age,
11 injury, disease and illness, and noise exposure; and
12 WHEREAS, SLPs and audiologists are among the health care professionals providing
13 hearing screenings, evaluations, diagnoses, treatments, and management for these hearing
14 losses as well as communication and swallowing disorders; and
