15 WHEREAS, many of the professionals of the Georgia Speech-Language-Hearing
16 Association serve Georgia's most vulnerable through the Medicaid, PeachCare for Kids, and
17 Babies Can't Wait programs; and
18 WHEREAS, the Georgia Speech-Language-Hearing Association's members are licensed
19 professionals, many of whom hold advanced degrees from accredited universities with
20 special training programs; and
21 WHEREAS, the Georgia Speech-Language-Hearing Association's members may be found
22 providing services in various settings, including hospitals, nursing homes, rehabilitation
23 centers, clinics, physicians' offices, private practices, client homes, pre-K through grade 12
24 schools, universities, and government and military practices; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
26 distinguished organization be appropriately honored for the health care and educational
27 services its members provide to Georgia's citizens.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
29 recognize and commend the Georgia Speech-Language-Hearing Association and its members
30 for their many years of tireless, efficient, effective, and dedicated service to the citizens of
31 this state as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
33 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Georgia
34 Speech-Language-Hearing Association.
